CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 20, 1962, pg. 1 reads:"Discussing Homewood-Brushton Renewal Plans - Key figures in plans to rejuvenate the Homewood-Brushton area through a proposed urban renewal project addressed a large, enthusiastic crowd attending an open meeting of the Homewood-Brushton Citizens Renewal Council. Seated before the group at a table in background are: Francis Holahan, chairman of the by-laws committee; George Davis, acting as president of the body, and William S. Howell, secretary and president of the cooperating Homewood Community Improvement Association. A small portion of the crowd can be seen in the foreground. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group of men and women seated in audience, including man wearing clerical collar seated in front row, during Homewood-Brushton Citizens Renewal Council meeting, in Homewood-Brushton YMCA
